Description: BRCore implements Shade and Stopnisek’s previously introduced workflow for core microbiome identification by using abundance-occupancy distributions and defines a microbial core based on its contribution to beta diversity (i.e. Bray-Curtis similarity) when compared to the entire dataset using a prioritizing variable used for occurrence detection. Functions leverage phyloseq objects and produce publication-ready figures, enabling reproducible microbiome analysis for bioenergy research.
